node.text:
On this occasion of #GaneshChaturthi we wish Lord Ganapati visits your home with bags full of happiness, prosperity and peace.?
This drawing is something very special, tried to draw #KarpakaVinayakar . Karpaka Vinayaka Templeor#PillaiyarpattiPillaiyar 
Temple is one of the oldest Cave Temples (Rock Cut) of Tamilnadu.
Karpaga Vinayagar is carved out in a cave of Pillaiyarpatti Hillocks. The Vinayagar sannidhi (Sanctom Sanctorum) is a cave where the 6 feet of Karpaga Vinayagar has been carved inside that faces north direction. Here Lord Vinayaga appears with 2 hands unlike in other places where he is seen with 4 hands.Also he is seen seated without Angusapasam, with his legs folded and stomach not touching the Asanam in the form of "Artha Padma" Asanam. Vinayagar’s trunk is curved at the right side (Valampuri Vinayagar) which is unique feature.
.
This temple is the only one in Tamil Nadu which contains a 6 feet rock-cut Vinayaka deity. This temple is one of the nine important temples for #Nagarathar
.
The word Vinayaga means "Incomparable Leader" Devotees worshipping Valamburi Vinayagar seated facing towards north, will be blessed with all wealth.

@_.gothi_  thanks for the patience ?
.
.
Here is some tips for y'all~

1.Facetime is the best for virtual shoots because of the dedicated snapshot button and trust me I've tried a bunch of other apps.

2.Turn on the live photos in iOS facetime settings so that you can snapshot the screen with the same quality of your/model's camera.

3.Use the rear camera for shooting to reduce noises and for a better depth of field.

4.Screen record the entire session and you'll thank me later.

5.The non-boring non-technical bit: The image quality is not going to be great! Embrace it!

Have fun shooting ?
.
.
.
.
